.TH MOR 1 "2026-04-01" "mor 0.14.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mor \- AI-accessible knowledge you actually own
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mor
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ query... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mor
stores knowledge as plain markdown files with YAML frontmatter on your disk,
indexed by SQLite FTS5 with optional vector embeddings. AI assistants access
your knowledge via MCP. You also get a CLI and HTTP API.
.PP
Memories are stored in
.I ~/.config/mor/memories/
(overridable via
.BR MOR_HOME ).
Each memory has an ID (UUID), title, optional description, tags, type, and
markdown content.
.PP
All commands accept multi-word queries without quoting. Options must come before
the query:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor find \-\-limit 5 python naming
mor cat fastify server primer
.fi
.RE
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Search
.TP
.BI "find " "query..."
Full-text search using FTS5 (tokenized, stemmed). When embeddings are configured,
results are merged using Reciprocal Rank Fusion. Frequently accessed memories
get a small ranking boost.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-l ", " \-\-limit " " n
Max results (default 20).
.TP
.BI \-s ", " \-\-threshold " " n
Minimum relevance score 0\-1 (default 0.3).
.RE
.TP
.BI "grep " "pattern..."
Search memory content by substring or regex.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " " n
Max results (default 20).
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore\-case
Case-insensitive matching.
.TP
.BR \-E ", " \-\-regex
Treat pattern as a JavaScript regular expression.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-word\-regexp
Match whole words only.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-line\-number
Show line numbers.
.TP
.BI \-A ", " \-\-after\-context " " n
Show n lines after each match.
.TP
.BI \-B ", " \-\-before\-context " " n
Show n lines before each match.
.TP
.BI \-C ", " \-\-context " " n
Show n lines before and after each match.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-files\-with\-matches
Show only memory titles, no matching lines.
.RE
.SS Create and Edit
.TP
.BI "add " "[file|url]"
Add a memory from a file, URL, stdin, or \fB$EDITOR\fR. Without arguments,
opens the editor.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-t ", " \-\-title " " title
Memory title.
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-description " " text
Short description.
.TP
.BI \-\-tags " " tags
Comma-separated tags.
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
Memory type (see \fBTYPES\fR).
.RE
.TP
.BI "edit " "query..."
Open a memory in \fB$EDITOR\fR.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Edit frontmatter too.
.RE
.TP
.BI "update " "query..."
Update metadata or content of an existing memory. Options must come before the query.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-t ", " \-\-title " " title
New title.
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-description " " text
New description.
.TP
.BI \-\-tags " " tags
New tags (comma-separated).
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
New type.
.TP
.BI \-\-content\-from " " source
Read new content from file or \fB\-\fR for stdin.
.RE
.SS Read and Export
.TP
.BI "cat " "query..."
Print memory content to stdout.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Include YAML frontmatter.
.TP
.B \-\-links
Show cross-references after the content.
.RE
.TP
.BI "cp " "query..."
Copy memory content to a file.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-o ", " \-\-output " " dest
Destination file path (required).
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Include YAML frontmatter.
.RE
.SS Cross-references
.TP
.BI "links " "[query...]"
Show forward links and backlinks for a memory.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-broken
List all memories with broken (dangling) references.
.RE
.PP
Memories can link to each other using markdown links with the \fBmor:\fR scheme:
.PP
.RS
.nf
[Fastify Chaos Plugin](mor:22f6b489)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Links use \fB\(->>\fR for forward, \fB<<\-\fR for backlinks, and \fB<<\->>\fR for
bidirectional. They are derived from content and optional frontmatter
\fBlinks\fR arrays, rebuilt on every upsert and reindex.
.SS Manage
.TP
.BI "rm " "id..."
Remove a memory by UUID or UUID prefix (8+ characters).
.TP
.B ls
List all memories, sorted by last updated.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-n ", " \-\-limit " " n
Max results.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-long
Show type, date, tags, and file path.
.TP
.B \-\-tags
List all tags with counts.
.TP
.B \-\-types
List all types with counts.
.RE
.TP
.B sync
Pull remote changes via git, commit and push local changes.
.TP
.B reindex
Rebuild the search index and links table from memory files.
.TP
.BI "import " dir
Import \fI.md\fR files from a directory.
.SS Server
.TP
.B mcp
Start an MCP server over stdio. Used by AI assistants.
.TP
.B serve
Start an HTTP server for remote access.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-p ", " \-\-port " " port
Listen port (default 7677).
.TP
.BI \-H ", " \-\-host " " host
Listen host (default 127.0.0.1).
.TP
.BI \-\-token " " token
Require Bearer token authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-mcp
Enable MCP endpoint at \fI/mcp\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B version
Show version information.
.TP
.BI "login"
Authenticate with a remote server via OAuth.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-s ", " \-\-server " " url
Server URL.
.RE
.SH FILTER OPTIONS
The following options are available for
.BR find ,
.BR grep ,
and
.BR ls :
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
Filter by memory type (comma-separated, glob patterns).
.TP
.BI \-\-tag " " pattern
Filter by tag (comma-separated, AND logic, glob patterns).
.TP
.BI \-\-repo " " pattern
Filter by repository (glob pattern).
.TP
.BI \-\-ext " " ext
Filter by file extension.
.SH TYPES
.TP
.B knowledge
General knowledge (default).
.TP
.B snippet
Code snippet.
.TP
.B file
Saved file.
.TP
.B user
User preferences and profile.
.TP
.B feedback
Workflow feedback and corrections.
.TP
.B project
Project context and decisions.
.TP
.B reference
Pointers to external resources.
.SH QUERY RESOLUTION
When a command accepts a
.IR query ,
it is resolved in order: full UUID, UUID prefix (8+ characters), filename,
then full-text search.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MOR_HOME
Override the configuration directory (default \fI~/.config/mor\fR).
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor used by
.B add
and
.BR edit .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/config.json
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/credentials.json
OAuth tokens (created by \fBmor login\fR).
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/memories/
Memory storage directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/index.db
SQLite search index (memories, FTS, links, embeddings).
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file supports:
.TP
.B memoryDir
Path to memory storage directory.
.TP
.B dbPath
Path to SQLite database.
.TP
.B autosync
Automatically git sync after add, update, and remove (boolean).
.TP
.B embedding
Embedding provider configuration (openai, azure-openai, ollama, none).
.TP
.B server
Remote server connection (url, token).
.TP
.B serve
HTTP server defaults (port, host, token, mcp).
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a memory from a file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor add src/utils.ts
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search for memories:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor find authentication flow
.fi
.RE
.PP
Grep for an exact string:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor grep \-i createServer
.fi
.RE
.PP
Grep with a regex:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor grep \-E "async\\s+function" \-i
.fi
.RE
.PP
List memories tagged with "config":
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor ls \-\-tag config
.fi
.RE
.PP
Update tags on a memory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor update \-\-tags "go,concurrency" 8da8d8f2
.fi
.RE
.PP
Copy a memory to a file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor cp \-o ./out.md fastify server primer
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show cross-references for a memory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor links fastify chaos plugin
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start the HTTP server with auth and MCP:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor serve \-\-token secret \-\-mcp
.fi
.RE
